gametext: *\b Deploy\b0  on an unoccupied Dagobah site. At the beginning of each of your move phases, opponent may relocate this Jedi Test to an adjacent site. *\b Target\b0  a mentor on Dagobah and an apprentice who has completed Jedi Test #1. Apprentice may move only by using personal landspeed. *\b Attempt\b0  when apprentice is present at the beginning of your control phase. Draw training destiny. If destiny + apprentice's ability > 13, test completed: *\b Place\b0  on apprentice. Apprentice is power +1 and may move normally. Total ability of 6 or more is required for opponent to draw battle destiny.
name: A Jedi's Strength

gametext: Insert in opponent's Reserve Deck. When Effect reaches top it is lost, but opponent must initiate a battle by the end of opponent's next battle phase or lose 4 Force. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: "The dark side of the Force are they. Easily they flow, quick to join you in a fight."
name: Anger, Fear, Aggression

dark_side_text: Your Ugnaughts deploy free aboard starships here. If you control, all your Ugnaughts on table are forfeit +2.
gametext: If opponent initiates a battle here, your starships may move as a 'react' to or from nearest related asteroid sector.   Your Ugnaughts deploy free aboard starships here. If you control, all your Ugnaughts on table are forfeit +2.
light_side_text: If opponent initiates a battle here, your starships may move as a 'react' to or from nearest related asteroid sector.
name: Anoat

dark_side_text: "Asteroid Rules" in effect here.
gametext: "Asteroid Rules" in effect here. If you control, may cancel Force drain at related system.   "Asteroid Rules" in effect here.
light_side_text: "Asteroid Rules" in effect here. If you control, may cancel Force drain at related system.
name: Asteroid Field

gametext: Deploy on any asteroid sector you control. During each of your control phases, opponent loses X Force, where X = total number of asteroid sectors at same system that are not occupied by opponent. Effect canceled if opponent controls this location.
lore: Smugglers and other criminals sometimes hide in asteroids to avoid capture. The larger the asteroid field, the more resources have to be devoted to the pursuit.
name: Asteroid Sanctuary

gametext: Deploy on any asteroid sector. Target one opponent's capital starship. Pilots aboard target may not use ability to draw battle destiny. Subtract 4 from asteroid destiny when targeting that starship. Utinni Effect canceled when reached by target.
lore: The personal fears of Vader's minions do not affect his priorities.
name: Asteroids Do Not Concern Me

gametext: Deploy on your starfighter. While an astromech character is aboard: If not piloted, starfighter may move and may use power, maneuver and hyperspeed. OR If piloted, starfighter is immune to attrition < 3 (< 6 if matching pilot aboard).
lore: Standard technology found on hyperdrive-capable starfighters. Many manufacturers. Converts electronic impulses and high-density electronic languages into readable text.
name: Astromech Translator

gametext: Deploy on an apprentice at the beginning of your turn. Apprentice 'rests' (may not attempt Jedi Tests) until end of your next turn, then relocate Immediate Effect to Jedi Test. When attempting this test, that apprentice adds 3 to training destiny. (Immune to Control.)
lore: To recover from the strenuous Jedi training routine and revitalize the mind and body, an apprentice must rest to be calm and at peace.
name: At Peace

gametext: USED: If a lightsaber was just used to enhance a Force drain, place it in owner's Used Pile. LOST: Place any or all of your devices and character weapons on table in your Used Pile.
lore: "I mean you no harm."
name: Away Put Your Weapon

dark_side_text: "Asteroid Rules" in effect here. If you control, Force drain +1 here.
gametext: "Asteroid Rules" in effect here. If you control, Force drain +1 here for each Asteroid Field at same system.   "Asteroid Rules" in effect here. If you control, Force drain +1 here.
light_side_text: "Asteroid Rules" in effect here. If you control, Force drain +1 here for each Asteroid Field at same system.
name: Big One

dark_side_text: "Cave Rules" in effect here.
gametext: "Cave Rules" in effect here. If you control, may cancel Force drains at system related to Big One.   "Cave Rules" in effect here.
light_side_text: "Cave Rules" in effect here. If you control, may cancel Force drains at system related to Big One.
name: Big One: Asteroid Cave or Space Slug Belly

gametext: Use 1 Force to cause all Mynocks or Vine Snakes to detach from one starfighter or character. OR Cause one Mynock attached to any starfighter to be lost. OR After a creature has selected a target character, cancel that selection and select again.
lore: "I just got this bucket back together. I'm not gonna let something tear it apart."
name: Blasted Varmints

gametext: * Ferocity = destiny - 1. Habitat: Dagobah. Parasite: Character (that can move). Relocate Bog-wing and host up to two sites away (opponent of victim chooses). Bog-wing then detaches.
lore: Large, flying jungle predator. One to five meters long, including tail. Swoops down and grasps victims in its claws. Young are born in mid-flight, as the mother drops from extreme altitude.
name: Bog-wing

gametext: During your move phase, use 1 Force to relocate your starship (free if a smuggler aboard) from a planet system to any related asteroid sector (or vice versa). OR Cancel Rogue Asteroid or Close Call.
lore: "I'm going in closer to one of those big ones." "Closer?!" "Closer?!" "Graarg?!"
name: Closer?!

gametext: Cancel Sense or Alter. (Immune to Sense.) OR Cancel one Immediate Effect, Mobile Effect or Force drain.
lore: Mystical Jedi power. Covers power of inner mind and body. Allows Jedi to exist in harmony with nature. You must learn this.
name: Control

dark_side_text: Neither player may Force drain here.
gametext: During your deploy phase, you may deploy one Dagobah site directly from Reserve Deck. Shuffle, cut and replace.   Neither player may Force drain here.
light_side_text: During your deploy phase, you may deploy one Dagobah site directly from Reserve Deck. Shuffle, cut and replace.
name: Dagobah

dark_side_text: If you occupy, Force generation +1 for you here.
gametext: Your starfighters may deploy here and are immune to Awwww, Cannot Get Your Ship Out here.   If you occupy, Force generation +1 for you here.
light_side_text: Your starfighters may deploy here and are immune to Awwww, Cannot Get Your Ship Out here.
name: Dagobah: Bog Clearing

dark_side_text: No starships or vehicles here. If you occupy, Force generation +1 for you here.
gametext: No starships or vehicles here. Your creatures are deploy -2 here.   No starships or vehicles here. If you occupy, Force generation +1 for you here.
light_side_text: No starships or vehicles here. Your creatures are deploy -2 here.
name: Dagobah: Jungle

dark_side_text: At end of your turn, your starships and vehicles here 'sink' to bottom of Lost Pile.
gametext: At end of your turn, your starships and vehicles here 'sink' to Used Pile.   At end of your turn, your starships and vehicles here 'sink' to bottom of Lost Pile.
light_side_text: At end of your turn, your starships and vehicles here 'sink' to Used Pile.
name: Dagobah: Swamp

dark_side_text: You may use 1 Force to cancel any Force drain here.
gametext: Once per turn, may take one Jedi Test into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.   You may use 1 Force to cancel any Force drain here.
light_side_text: Once per turn, may take one Jedi Test into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
name: Dagobah: Training Area

dark_side_text: If you occupy, opponent's Yoda's Hut game text is canceled.
gametext: If Yoda here, once per turn, may subtract 2 from attrition against you at another location.   If you occupy, opponent's Yoda's Hut game text is canceled.
light_side_text: If Yoda here, once per turn, may subtract 2 from attrition against you at another location.
name: Dagobah: Yoda's Hut

gametext: During your turn, if either player just placed a card in a Used Pile, deploy on table. All Used Piles are immediately re-circulated. When any player places one or more cards in a Used Pile, Immediate Effect canceled.
lore: Jedi training is a journey into the depths of an apprentice's subconscious, where one must learn to use the Force wisely. "A Jedi's strength flows from the Force."
name: Descent Into The Dark

gametext: Deploy on table. Sense and Alter are Lost Interrupts. Also, when any player makes a destiny draw for Sense or Alter, and that destiny draw is successful, that player loses 2 Force. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: A Jedi may choose to intervene in the natural course of events, but must accept responsibility for the consequences.
name: Do, Or Do Not

gametext: *\b Deploy\b0  on Dagobah: Jungle or Dagobah: Cave. *\b Target\b0  a mentor on Dagobah and an apprentice who has completed Jedi Test #2. *\b Attempt\b0  when apprentice is present at the end of your turn and none of your cards participated in battles, Force drains or Jedi Tests during that turn. Draw training destiny. If destiny + apprentice's ability > 14, test completed. *\b Place\b0  on apprentice. You may subtract 1 from each of opponent's destiny draws.
name: Domain Of Evil

gametext: Deploy on your R-unit droid. During any control phase, you may use 1 Force to peek at the top card of opponent's Reserve Deck. Also, if on Dagobah, droid may move for free.
lore: Full-spectrum transceiver for R-unit droids including electro-photo receptors, DERs and heat and motion detectors. Data is routed directly to droids Intellex IV internal computer.
name: Droid Sensorscope

gametext: USED: Cancel Limited Resources. LOST: Use 3 Force to retrieve into hand one Effect of any kind.
lore: When the nav computer maintenance program failed to auto-repair the hyperdrive, Han decided to take matters into his own hand.
name: Effective Repairs

gametext: During opponent's control phase, if opponent has two or more capital starships at a system or sector together, draw destiny. If destiny - 1 < number of those starships, they may not move or participate in battle until end of your next turn.
lore: Details of the notorious "Incident at Anoat" are required reading at the Imperial Academy of Raithal, where the pilots' names are posthumously displayed.
name: Egregious Pilot Error

gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on any exterior planet site where you have a Rebel or alien. You may deploy characters at this site, even without presence, regardless of location deployment restrictions.
lore: Pirates, smugglers and Rebels operate from tiny camps which can be set up quickly and relocated at a moment's notice. A surprise visitor made Luke an unhappy camper.
name: Encampment

gametext: Deploy on your side of table. At any time, you may use 3 Force to draw the top card of your Reserve Deck into your hand. If that card is a space creature, you may immediately deploy it for free.
lore: Occasionally Han was capable of such feats, even without Threepio there to tell him these things.
name: Flash Of Insight

gametext: If you have a character of ability > 4 on table, use 3 Force to find one of your missing characters (your choice). OR During any control phase, examine the top card of your Lost Pile. If that card is a character of ability < 3, take that character into hand.
lore: "I'm looking for someone." "Looking? Found someone you have I would say."
name: Found Someone You Have

gametext: *\b Deploy\b0  on a Dagobah site. *\b Target\b0  a mentor here. Also, target or deploy (regardless of location deployment restrictions) an apprentice here. *\b Attempt\b0  when targets are present at the beginning of your control phase. Draw training destiny. If destiny + apprentice's ability > 12, test completed: *\b Place\b0  on apprentice. All opponent's Force drain bonuses are canceled. \ul Mentor: Your character of ability > 2. Apprentice: Your non-droid, non-Jedi character of lesser ability than mentor. Each time you complete any Jedi Test, you may exchange one card in hand for one Jedi Test in your Lost Pile.\ul
name: Great Warrior

gametext: Deploy on a landed starship (not at a docking bay). Starship may not move. OR Deploy on a starship or vehicle on Dagobah. Starship or vehicle may not move. At the start of your next control phase, starship or vehicle 'sinks' to bottom of the Lost Pile.
lore: "If you're saying coming here was a bad idea, I'm beginning to agree with you."
name: Grounded Starfighter

gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on one of you characters, vehicles or starships (free on \ul Falcon\ul0  or Han). While aboard a vehicle or starship, you may use 1 Force to cancel any Interrupt or Effect of any kind which targets that vehicle or starship.
lore: Experienced pilots keep a well equipped toolkit. Horizontal boosters, alluvial dampers and hydrospanners aid in performing high-tech repairs aboard starships.
name: Han's Toolkit

gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on your side of table. At any time, you may declare a card type. Use your Force one by one, revealing each card used, until a card of that type is revealed (take it into hand) or Force Pile is depleted.
lore: Rebels often exploit loopholes in Imperial procedures to gain an advantage.
name: Hiding In The Garbage

gametext: Use 3 Force: Retarget an Interrupt or Utinni Effect which specifies a target to another appropriate target on the same side of the Force. OR Relocate any Effect (except those immune to Alter) deployed on a location to another appropriate location.
lore: "This ground sure feels strange. Doesn't feel like rock. I don't know..."
name: I Have A Bad Feeling About This

gametext: Deploy on any Effect or Utinni Effect (except those immune to Alter). During each of owner's draw phases, if you occupy an asteroid sector, owner must choose to either lose 1 Force or voluntarily cancel that Effect or Utinni Effect. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: To succeed in the Imperial Navy, an officer must be willing to take risks. Difficult choices must be made.
name: Ineffective Maneuver

gametext: *\b Deploy\b0  on a Dagobah site. *\b Target\b0  a mentor on Dagobah and an apprentice who has completed Jedi Test #4. *\b Attempt\b0  when apprentice is present at the beginning of your control phase. Turn apprentice upside down (cannot move and power = 0). At the end of your next turn, turn apprentice right side up (restored): *\b Place\b0  on apprentice. Immune to attrition < 4. Reveal the top two cards of your Reserve Deck and place one upside down on apprentice. Whenever you are about to draw a card for destiny, you may instead use the upside-down card (which remains on apprentice for re-use).
name: It Is The Future You See

gametext: Use X Force, where X = (7 - ability of your highest-ability character on table). Take one card from Used Pile into hand; reshuffle.
lore: A Jedi can adjust the force within and around an object, causing it to move as the Jedi wills.
name: Jedi Levitation

gametext: Deploy on your starfighter. During any control phase, may target one opponent's capital starship present. Starfighter attaches to target (automatically moves with target and is 'concealed'). May detach at any time (even as target begins to move).
lore: Special modification for starfighters. Size may vary depending on mass of starship. Allows a stable connection to a spacedock, uneven terrain or even another starship.
name: Landing Claw

gametext: USED: Cancel Silence is Golden or Shut Him Up Or Shut Him Down. LOST: Take any one droid, device or Stone Pile into hand from Used Pile; reshuffle.
lore: Telekinesis is one of the powers awakened during a Jedi's apprenticeship. Using this ability, a student of the Force can learn to levitate objects.
name: Levitation

gametext: Cancel Dark Maneuvers, Emergency Deployment, Lone Pilot, I Want That Ship, Defensive Fire, Rogue Asteroid or Take Evasive Action. OR Double Special Modifications until end of turn.
lore: Rookie TIE pilots often fail to grasp the gravity of their situation and are easily lured into compromising positions.
name: Light Maneuvers

gametext: Target one opponent's starfighter present with your starship at an asteroid sector, before asteroid destiny is drawn this turn. If target lost this turn due to asteroid destiny, opponent also loses Force equal to target's forfeit value.
lore: Asteroid fields require starfighters to act as comm relays, forwarding orders to the squadron via subspace AE-35 Transceivers. If ships are lost, communications break down.
name: Lost Relay

gametext: Deploy on your character. May carry and use any number of devices. May also carry Yoda, Kabe or any one Jawa or Ewok (as if riding a creature vehicle). Adds 1 to training destiny when carrying the mentor.
lore: Made on Dantooine. Luke used the many pockets in his gundark-skin backpack to carry supplies while on patrol.
name: Luke's Backpack

gametext: Target one starfighter participating in a battle at a system or sector. For remainder of turn, starfighter may not move, is immune to attrition and, if piloted by any Corellian, is power +2.
lore: Sometimes the best defense is an insane offense.
name: Moving To Attack Position

gametext: Habitat: unlimited. Parasite: Starfighter. Host's power and hyperspeed are \b cumulatively\b0  -2; while both < 1, Mynocks randomly detach one at a time (cannot attach for remainder of turn). Moves like a starfighter.
lore: Starship parasite. Flourishes in vacuum of space. Consumes radiation and other forms of energy. Chews on power cables. Adults have one-meter wingspan. Reproduces by macromiosis.
name: Mynock

gametext: Insert in opponent's Reserve Deck. When Effect reaches top it is lost and up to the three lowest destiny numbers of each player's characters on table are totaled. Player with lower total loses Force equal to the difference. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: "You said you wanted to be around when I made a mistake, well, this could be it, sweetheart."
name: Never Tell Me The Odds

gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on your side of table. If a Rebel of ability > 2 is lost (not captured) during a battle involving an opponent's bounty hunter, opponent loses 3 Force. If Vader on table, one bounty hunter involved in that battle (your choice) is also lost.
lore: "There will be a substantial reward for the one who finds the \ul Millennium Falcon\ul0. You are free to use any methods necessary, but I want them alive."
name: No Disintegrations!

gametext: * Ferocity = destiny - 4. Habitat: planet sites (except Hoth and Tatooine) and Dark Waters. \b Cumulatively\b0  absorbs (temporarily cancels) one (Dark Side Force icon) icon present. Parasite: None.
lore: Tree-nesting reptile. Favors moist caves and marshes. Extremely docile, despite fearsome appearance. Responsive to Force energy.
name: Nudj

gametext: Use 4 Force to deploy at any site if opponent is generating at least 3 Force more than you. At that site, adjacent sites and same sites as Obi-Wan, players activate Force only if they have presence.
lore: "Luminous beings are we, not this crude matter." The inner consciousness of a Jedi can transcend even death.
name: Obi-Wan's Apparition

gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on opponent's side of table. At the end of each of opponent's battle phases, if a battle did not take place at every location where both players have presence at the end of that phase, opponent loses 3 Force.
lore: Political pressure forced the Empire to join battle with the Alliance in otherwise tactically poor situations. Failure to engage the enemy was considered tantamount to treason.
name: Order To Engage

gametext: Deploy on table. Turn every Used Pile face up. All subsequent cards placed in Used Piles are also turned face up. (Players must commit to using cards before revealing them.) Turn used cards face down whenever they are re-circulated.
lore: Imbalance in a converter's inverse energy field can improperly polarize the negative axis, causing hyperdrive failure. Replacement often requires an inverted engineer.
name: Polarized Negative Power Coupling

gametext: Deploy on your warrior. When that warrior fires a blaster rifle or artillery weapon, adds 1 to each of that weapon's destiny draws. Also, may add 1 to power of one droid present.
lore: Lardanis Survival Systems MFCR-200 Power Generator. Used by smugglers and Rebel agents. Highly portable. Powers and charges a wide range of equipment.
name: Portable Fusion Generator

gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Once during each of your draw phases, you may use 2 Force to take any one blaster from your Lost pile and deploy it (for free).
lore: It's high moon on Dagobah, his droid's reined in and Luke's got a fistful of credits.
name: Quick Draw

dark_side_text: If you control, you may raise your converted Raithal system to the top.
gametext: If you control, all opponent's troopers are forfeit and destiny -1.   If you control, you may raise your converted Raithal system to the top.
light_side_text: If you control, all opponent's troopers are forfeit and destiny -1.
name: Raithal

gametext: Deploy on your pilot character. While piloting any starfighter, combat vehicle or shuttle vehicle, that character is considered to be the "matching pilot" (pilot adds 2 to maneuver (limit +2) and draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise).
lore: Pilot fatigues feature digital technology which can be customized for particular starfighters. Increases interface efficiency with a newly assigned craft.
name: Rebel Flight Suit

gametext: Use 3 Force. Each player places hand onto Reserve Deck (if possible), then places Used Pile onto Reserve deck; reshuffle. Each player then draws cards from Reserve Deck equal to the number of cards just placed from hand onto Reserve Deck (if any).
lore: In combat, a bold and unexpected move can change the entire situation.
name: Recoil In Fear

gametext: Deploy on Leia. Once during each of your control phases, you may use 3 Force to retrieve 1 Force. Also, when an apprentice, adds 1 to her training destiny.
lore: It was hard to imagine the enormous losses the Alliance suffered during the Battle of Hoth. Leia contemplated what she could do to help the Rebellion recover.
name: Reflection

gametext: If you just won a battle, deploy on Vader. Target an Imperial involved in that battle. Vader and target are power and forfeit -4. When target reaches Vader, lose Utinni Effect and draw destiny. If destiny > 2, target lost.
lore: An evil Lord of the Sith, Darth Vader used fear as a powerful motivational factor. The Emperor demanded results. Vader settled for no less.
name: Report To Lord Vader

gametext: Deploy on your R-unit droid to give that droid \b thief\b0  skill. Once during each of your control phases, you may use 1 Force to target a weapon or device present. Draw destiny. If destiny > 2, target is 'stolen.' Target may then be transferred for free. Droid may not be Disarmed.
lore: 2 kilo lifting capacity and .85 meter reach. Better than 1 micrometer placement accuracy. Feisty Rebel droids can use this tool for sneaky purposes.
name: Retractable Arm

gametext: Deploy on an asteroid sector and specify starting direction. Every move phase, moves to next adjacent asteroid sector (reversing direction as necessary). Where present, adds 2 to asteroid destiny. May be targeted by starship weapons (defense value = 3).
lore: "Considering the amount of damage we've sustained, they must have been destroyed."
name: Rogue Asteroid

gametext: Deploy on a Big One. X = twice the number of asteroid sectors at that system. Target a starfighter at related planet system. When reached by target, relocate Utinni Effect to planet system. When target returns to system, lose Utinni Effect. Retrieve X Force.
lore: The infamous smuggler Rycar Ryjerd does this all the time. He's an idiot.
name: Rycar's Run

gametext: Deploy on opponent's side of table. Opponent's pilots (except Vader) present at sites may not use ability to draw battle destiny. Effect canceled when opponent has no pilots at sites.
lore: Pilots at ground bases throughout the Empire were immediately recalled to their ships to assist in the capture of the Rebels fleeing Echo Base on Hoth.
name: Scramble

gametext: If you have a droid on table: Cancel an attack just initiated by a creature. OR Move one opponent's creature (except an attached creature) to an adjacent location (habitat permitting).
lore: "Oh! Go away! Go away! Beastly thing!"
name: Shoo! Shoo!

gametext: *\b Deploy\b0  on Dagobah: Swamp or Dagobah: Bog Clearing. *\b Target\b0  a mentor on Dagobah and an apprentice who has completed Jedi Test #3. *\b Attempt\b0  when apprentice is present at the beginning of your control phase. Draw training destiny. If destiny + apprentice's ability > 15, test completed: *\b Place\b0  on apprentice. Immune to attrition < 3. Once during each of your control phases, you may use 2 Force to take any one card into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
name: Size Matters Not

gametext: Deploy on a smuggler. May use 2 Force to cancel Limited Resources. Also, if 'trained' by Rycar Ryjerd and piloting a starship when that starship completes Kessel Run, Rycar's Run or The First Transport Is Away, any retrieved Force may be taken into hand.
lore: It's the lure of easy credits. It's got a very strong appeal. Perhaps you'd understand better wearing my flight suit. It's the ultimate special modification, it's the smuggler's blues.
name: Smuggler's Blues

gametext: Deploys only on Dagobah or Cloud City. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Once per game, during your deploy phase, a lightsaber may deploy on Luke (for free) from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Immune to attrition < 4.
lore: Luke Skywalker. Son of Anakin. Seeker of Yoda. Levitator of rocks. Ignorer of advice. Incapable of impossible. Reckless is he.
name: Son Of Skywalker

gametext: * Ferocity = two destiny. Habitat: Big One (Cave is now Belly). Attacks starfighters (defeated cards are eaten or relocated to Belly, opponent of victim chooses). Once per turn, may open or close mouth.
lore: Immense spaceborn predator. Consumes minerals, mynocks and the occasional passing starfighter. Lives in asteroid caves. Only one meter long at birth.
name: Space Slug

gametext: USED: Cancel Awwww, Cannot Get Your Ship Out. LOST: Use 1 Force to draw destiny. If destiny < ability of you highest-ability character on table, take one starship into hand from Used Pile; reshuffle.
lore: A Jedi can move large objects with the power of the mind.
name: Starship Levitation

gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on any Dagobah site. Randomly select two cards from opponent's hand and place them, unseen, face down beneath Stone Pile. Cards return to opponent's hand if Effect leaves table. Canceled if opponent occupies this site.
lore: "Use the Force. Yes... Now, the stone. Feel it."
name: Stone Pile

gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on your side of table (free if C-3PO on table). If you have a protocol droid aboard a starship or vehicle in a battle, you may use X Force to reduce the battle damage against you by X (by X+1 if a astromech character is also aboard).
lore: Protocol droids are programmed to interface with a variety of computer technologies. Quick and precise interpretation can dramatically increase operational efficiency.
name: The Professor

gametext: Use 1 Force to target a starship at an asteroid sector or a "blown away" system. For remainder of turn, you may add 2 to destiny totals targeting the armor or maneuver of that starship.
lore: Flying into an asteroid field is considered to be certain death except by Han Solo, Rycar Ryjerd and the terminally insane.
name: They'd Be Crazy To Follow Us

gametext: During a battle, lose X Force to reduce attrition against you by X. OR Cancel This Is Just Wrong.
lore: "You like me because I'm a scoundrel. There aren't enough scoundrels in your life." "I happen to like nice men." "I'm a nice man." "No you're not, you're ..."
name: This Is More Like It

gametext: Relocate one starfighter from a Big One to the related site (or vice versa) for free (opens Slug's mouth if closed). If smuggler aboard, starfighter is immune to attrition and subtracts 5 from asteroid destiny until end of your next turn. OR Cancel Corrosive Damage.
lore: The largest space slug on record was 900 meters long. Han suspected he had discovered one that was somewhat larger.
name: This Is No Cave

gametext: At the end of any player's draw phase, cause that player to place Used Pile face up on top of Reserve Deck; reshuffle. When face up cards are removed from Reserve Deck, they are treated as normal (no longer face up).
lore: One training exercise for a Jedi's apprentice is to invert one's view to see things from a different perspective. "The future, the past. Old friends long gone."
name: Through The Force Things You Will See

gametext: If you have a lone vehicle or starfighter in a battle or Attack Run at Beggar's Canyon, Cloud City, Death Star: Trench or an asteroid sector, use 1 Force. At the end of that battle or Attack Run, opponent must forfeit two participating vehicles or starfighters.
lore: Rebel pilots often join the Rebellion from Outer Rim worlds. Bush pilots fly by the seat of their pants, giving them a huge advantage in close quarters.
name: Tight Squeeze

gametext: Cancel one hologram. OR Use 3 Force. Draw destiny. Add 1 to destiny for each asteroid sector on table. If total destiny > 3, Imperial Holotable site is "blown away" (opponent loses 4 Force).
lore: After the mission, the Death Squadron HoloNet communications system reported fifteen system errors: ten computer malfunctions, four power failures and one asteroid.
name: Transmission Terminated

gametext: Take one card into hand from Force pile; reshuffle.
lore: Han could always see the light at the end of the tunnel.
name: Tunnel Vision

gametext: Habitat: planet sites (except Hoth). Parasite: Non-droid character. Each move phase, draw destiny; each time destiny > ability, add 1 to X (X starts at 0). Host is power -X (eaten if power = 0).
lore: Constricts hapless victims. Prey usually struggles at first, then weakens as strength diminishes. Difficult to spot. Common hazard on less-developed worlds.
name: Vine Snake

gametext: Name an Interrupt card. Opponent must reveal entire Used Pile, without shuffling. Then you choose: USED: Opponent must lose 1 Force for each copy of that Interrupt found there. LOST: Each copy of that interrupt found there is lost.
lore: It's 15 parsecs to Kessel, we've replaced the negative power coupling, it's dark and we're wearing welding goggles. Hit it.
name: Visored Vision

gametext: If your character was just defeated by a Dragonsnake, Rancor, Sarlacc, Dianoga or Wampa, instead of being 'eaten' that character is 'hurled' (relocated) to an adjacent site, if possible.
lore: "You're lucky you don't taste very good."
name: WHAAAAAAAAAOOOOW!

gametext: Deploy on any location. For either player to initiate a battle or Force drain anywhere, that player must use +1 Force. Effect canceled if opponent controls this location.
lore: A Jedi seeks nonviolent solutions to problems, but may fight to preserve the existence of life. An apprentice must learn which battles to fight and which to avoid.
name: Wars Not Make One Great

gametext: USED: Take one Collision! or Egregious Pilot Error into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. LOST: If opponent just initiated a battle with at least two capital starships where you have a lone starfighter, add two battle destiny.
lore: They're as clumsy as they are stupid.
name: We Can Still Outmaneuver Them

gametext: USED: Cancel Res Luk Ra'auf. LOST: If two bounty hunters (or an Imperial and a bounty hunter) are in a battle together, use 2 Force to draw two destiny. Subtract total from opponent's attrition and total power.
lore: Bounty Hunters. Independent contractors. Highly competitive loners. Powerful. Deadly. Scum.
name: We Don't Need Their Scum

gametext: Deploy on Emperor or any system. Target one character whose lore uses the word 'Emperor.' Target cannot use ability to draw battle destiny and is excluded from being the "highest-ability character." Utinni Effect canceled when reached by target.
lore: Reaching across the galaxy, the Emperor uses his vast powers to require immediate submission and obedience. His minions frequently find this inconvenient.
name: What Is Thy Bidding, My Master?

gametext: Deploy on Dagobah I must, but move elsewhere I may, yes. When the mentor, 1 to training destiny I add. Where present am I, battles and attacks happen not unless present a Dark Side character of ability > 3 there is. To attrition, immune am I.
lore: Help you I can, yes. For 800 years have I trained Jedi. Judge me by my size do you? Mm? And well you should not! For my ally is the Force... and a powerful ally it is.
name: Yoda

gametext: During opponent's turn, take up to four cards from your hand and place them on top of your Force Pile.
lore: "For the Jedi it is time to eat as well."
name: Yoda Stew

gametext: Deploy on Yoda. You may initiate battles and attacks where present. OR Use 2 Force to deploy on one of your characters of ability > 3. Immune to attrition. Where present, no battles or attacks may be initiated unless an opponent's character of ability > 3 present.
lore: A symbol of the Jedi Master and his ancient wisdom. Speak softly you may but a big stick you must carry, yes.
name: Yoda's Gimer Stick

gametext: Deploy on a character. When on the mentor, adds 1 to training destiny draws. If on Yoda, you may lose Effect to take one card with 'levitation' in the title from Reserve Deck into hand; reshuffle.
lore: "You must feel the Force around you. Here, between you, me, the tree, the rock, everywhere! Yes, even between the land and the ship."
name: Yoda's Hope

gametext: Use 1 Force to retrieve Yoda. OR Use 3 Force to take Yoda into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
lore: "Take you to him I will."
name: Yoda, You Seek Yoda

gametext: During a battle, before any cards have been forfeited, reduce all attrition for both sides to zero.
lore: Sarcastic, Sardonic, Irreverent. Impertinent. Exasperating. Disrespectful. Outrageous and charming. Han was a scoundrel but Leia began to realize that she loved him.
name: You Do Have Your Moments

gametext: Insert in opponent's Reserve Deck. When Effect reaches top it is lost and up to the three lowest destiny numbers of each player's characters on table are totaled. Player with lower total loses Force equal to the difference. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: What are the odds of having a Corellian, a Wookiee and a protocol droid together with an Alderaanian princess who happens to be the daughter of the Dark Lord of the Sith?
name: 3,720 To 1

characteristics: \b Black Sun agent\b0, \b bounty hunter\b0, \b information broker\b0, \b thief\b0
gametext: Total power at same site is +1 for each of your alien/droid pairs present. Once during each battle, if present with Zuckuss, may use 1 Force to search any Used Pile and relocate one character there to the lost pile. May initiate battle and be battled.
lore: \b Information broker\b0. \b Thief\b0. Overrode and reprogrammed its own self-governing software. Convinced Jabba the Hutt to upgrade its armor and weaponry. Became a \b bounty hunter\b0.
name: 4-LOM

gametext: Use 4 Force to deploy on your warrior, free on 4-LOM. May target a character or creature for free at same site or exterior site up to 2 sites away. Draw destiny. Add 1 if Blaster Scope attached. If total destiny - distance to target > defense value, target hit.
lore: BlasTech LJ-90. Not as accurate as the E-11 Blaster Rifle, but uses the same scope mount and has much better range. Acquired by 4-LOM after teaming up with Zuckuss.
name: 4-LOM's Concussion Rifle

gametext: USED: Peek at the cards in opponent's Force pile. Reorder however you wish and replace. LOST: Take one Dark Forces into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
lore: "This is a dangerous time for you, when you will be tempted by the dark side of the Force."
name: A Dangerous Time

dark_side_text: If opponent initiates a battle here, your starships may move as a 'react' to or from nearest related asteroid sector.
gametext: If you control, all opponent's Ugnaughts on table are forfeit -1.   If opponent initiates a battle here, your starships may move as a 'react' to or from nearest related asteroid sector.
light_side_text: If you control, all opponent's Ugnaughts on table are forfeit -1.
name: Anoat

gametext: At the end of any battle phase, lose one of your Imperials of ability < 6 who survived a battle you lost this turn. Activate Force up to either that character's forfeit value or the amount of your battle damage in that battle (your choice).
lore: "I shall assume full responsibility for losing them and apologize to Lord Vader." Needa discovered that Vader was only slightly more forgiving than the Emperor.
name: Apology Accepted

dark_side_text: "Asteroid Rules" in effect here. If you control, may cancel Force drain at related system.
gametext: "Asteroid Rules" in effect here.   "Asteroid Rules" in effect here. If you control, may cancel Force drain at related system.
light_side_text: "Asteroid Rules" in effect here.
name: Asteroid Field

gametext: May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, 2 vehicles, and 4 TIEs. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. Subtract 2 from asteroid destiny draws targeting \ul Avenger\ul0.
lore: Key starship used to subjugate Outer Rim worlds. Reassigned to Death Squadron under the command of Captain Needa. Communications ship at the Battle of Endor.
name: Avenger

gametext: Deploy on a landed starship (not at a docking bay). Starship may not move. OR Deploy on a starship or vehicle on Dagobah. Starship or vehicle may not move. At the start of you next control phase, starship or vehicle 'sinks' to the Used Pile.
lore: "Listen, friend, we didn't mean to land in that puddle, and if we could get our ship out, we would, but we can't so why don't you just..."
name: Awwww, Cannot Get Your Ship Out

gametext: Deploy on opponent's side of table. Luke, Leia, Han, Chewie, Lando, Yoda, and Obi-Wan are each deploy +2. Also, opponent may not play any cards with the words "bad feeling" in the title.
lore: "Ready are you? What know you of ready?"
name: Bad Feeling Have I

dark_side_text: "Asteroid Rules" in effect here. Force drain +1 here for each Asteroid Field at same system.
gametext: "Asteroid Rules" in effect here.   "Asteroid Rules" in effect here. Force drain +1 here for each Asteroid Field at same system.
light_side_text: "Asteroid Rules" in effect here.
name: Big One

dark_side_text: "Cave Rules" in effect here. If you control, may cancel Force drains at system related to Big One.
gametext: "Cave Rules" in effect here.   "Cave Rules" in effect here. If you control, may cancel Force drains at system related to Big One.
light_side_text: "Cave Rules" in effect here.
name: Big One: Asteroid Cave or Space Slug Belly

gametext: * Ferocity = destiny - 1. Habitat: Dagobah. Parasite: Character (that can move). Relocate Bog-wing and host up to two sites away (opponent of victim chooses). Bog-wing then detaches.
lore: Avian jungle-dweller. Fiercely territorial. Uses powerful talons to pick up and bear off victims. Carries up to nine times it's own body weight. Feeds primarily on root lizards and vine snakes.
name: Bog-wing

gametext: Deploy on a non-interior planet site (except Dagobah). May move to an adjacent non-interior site at start of your move phase. Your bombers at a related system you control may move to this site. Bombers must return to system at end of your battle phase (if possible).
lore: Bombers can sometimes slip past orbital defenses. Making a low-altitude bombing run allows "surgical strikes," even in cramped situations such as canyons and city streets.
name: Bombing Run

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting \ul Hound's Tooth\ul0, draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. Adds 1 to attrition against opponent in battles at same site. May reduce Chewie's forfeit to zero here.
lore: Male Trandoshan \b bounty hunter\b0. Strong but clumsy. Extremely proud and arrogant. Suffered a humiliating defeat at the hands of Chewbacca and his partner Han Solo.
name: Bossk

gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on Bossk, 4 on your other warrior. May fire using 2 Force. Draw destiny. If destiny > 0, one card with that destiny number at same site is lost (your choice). If destiny = 0, mortar gun explodes and warrior firing it is lost.
lore: Relby-v10 micro grenade launcher. Modified version of the limited range CSPL "Caspel" Projectile Launcher. Blows lots of stuff up.
name: Bossk's Mortar Gun

gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Apprentices subtract X from training destiny, where X = ability - Jedi Test number (minimum zero). Also, once per turn, you may use 2 Force to move the top card of opponent's Force Pile to the top of opponent's Reserve Deck.
lore: To effectively use the Force, a Jedi is required to learn concentration. A Jedi who gives in to distraction places both himself and his friends in peril.
name: Broken Concentration

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting \ul Avenger\ul0, that starship is also immune to attrition < 4. You may re-target applicable Utinni Effects to Needa. If in a battle where you choose to forfeit characters, you must forfeit Needa first.
lore: Able \b leader\b0  and captain of the \ul Avenger\ul0. Was given his command by Admiral Ozzel. Treated with suspicion by Darth Vader and the Emperor, who distrust Ozzel's close advisors.
name: Captain Needa

gametext: USED: Cancel one asteroid destiny and cause it to be drawn again. LOST: Lose 1 Force. Opponent must reveal the top card of Reserve Deck, Force Pile and Used Pile. Card(s) with lowest destiny number greater than zero are lost.
lore: If this little one doesn't pulverize you, the next one just might.
name: Close Call

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots, and that starship or vehicle moves for free.
lore: Chief Hudiss is one of the Imperial fleet's many communication specialists. Coordinates Star Destroyer fleet movement during challenging tactical situations.
name: Comm Chief

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Once during each of your control phases, when aboard a Star Destroyer or at any docking bay, may use 1 Force to take one TIE into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
lore: Technical Services Officer of the Fleet Support Branch. Responsible for keeping \ul Executor's\ul0  12 TIE squadrons serviced and combat ready. Just received transfer to \ul Judicator\ul0.
name: Commander Brandei

gametext: Once during each of your deploy phases, when aboard \ul Executor\ul0, may use 2 Force to take one \ul Executor\ul0  site into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
lore: Deck officer aboard the Super Star Destroyer \ul Executor\ul0. Responsible for preventing unauthorized access to sensitive areas of the Empire's flagship. Hand-picked by Captain Piett.
name: Commander Gherant

gametext: Adds 1 to power and maneuver of anything he pilots. Opponent may not 'react' to or from same location.
lore: Logistics officer for the \ul Avenger\ul0, member of the Line Branch of the Imperial Navy. Relays important scanner information to Captain Needa. Fiercely competitive.
name: Commander Nemet

gametext: Cancel Sense or Alter. (Immune to Sense.) OR Cancel one Immediate Effect, Mobile Effect or Force drain.
lore: Users of the Force can mysteriously manipulate their own physiology and psychology. Control allows rapid healing and provides some immunity to pain, poison and disease.
name: Control

gametext: Power +1 when at any \ul Executor\ul0  site. While at Detention Block Corridor, cancels game text of Detention Block Control Room. May use 1 Force take one IT-O or Hypo into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
lore: Member of Imperial Intelligence, Internal Security division. Assigned by IntSec to \ul Executor\ul0. Responsible for physical safety of Imperial personnel against Rebel saboteurs.
name: Corporal Derdram

gametext: May use 1 Force to take one Spice Mines Of Kessel or Detention Block Corridor into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. While Vandolay is at a mobile site, We Have A Prisoner is a Used Interrupt.
lore: ISB attache to the \ul Executor\ul0. Detention Officer. Political Liaison for COMPNOR. Responsible for all prisoner transfers. Fiercely loyal to the Emperor's New Order.
name: Corporal Vandolay

gametext: Deploy on Space Slug Belly. At the end of each player's turn, for every character and starship that player has present, that player must lose 1 Force. Effect canceled if Space Slug lost.
lore: The interior or a space slug's maw is mildly acidic. Long-term exposure to this corrosive environment can cause considerable damage.
name: Corrosive Damage

dark_side_text: If opponent occupies, your Force icons here are canceled.
gametext: Lose 1 force during each of your control phases if Yoda on table but not on Dagobah.   If opponent occupies, your Force icons here are canceled.
light_side_text: Lose 1 force during each of your control phases if Yoda on table but not on Dagobah.
name: Dagobah: Cave

gametext: Cancel Rogue Asteroid. OR Randomly select one card from opponent's hand and place it, unseen, in Used Pile.
lore: 275 gunners manning 60 turbolaser batteries provide a wide firing arc. Even so, asteroids are a challenge due to the sluggish recharge rates of the high-powered blasters.
name: Defensive Fire

characteristics: \b Black Sun agent\b0, \b bounty hunter\b0, \b Corellian\b0, \b assassin\b0
gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Power +1 for each opponent's character present. While present, may reduce Han's forfeit to zero here.
lore: Corellian \b bounty hunter\b0. Assassin trained by the Empire. Has reflex-enhancing cyber implants. Gravely injured during a swoop race in the crystal swamp of Agrilat. Blames Han Solo.
name: Dengar

gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on Dengar, 3 on your other warrior. May target a character, creature, or vehicle using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny +1 > defense value. If hit by Dengar, target's forfeit = 0.
lore: Rugged, reliable Valken-38 carbine. Excellent sniper's weapon in the hands of a competent marksman. Stolen from a victim when Dengar was working as an Imperial Assassin.
name: Dengar's Blaster Carbine

gametext: * Ferocity = 3 + destiny. Habitat: swamps, jungles and Dark Waters. May attack droids. Defeated droids are relocated to an adjacent exterior site (opponent of victim chooses).
lore: One of Dagobah's deadliest predators. Has razor-sharp fins, powerful constrictor coils and large fangs. Feeds on almost anything. Often mistaken for a swamp slug, due to its size.
name: Dragonsnake

gametext: May add unlimited pilots, passengers, vehicles and starfighters. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilots provide total ability of 3. Immune to attrition < 12.
lore: Flagship of Death Squadron. Over eight kilometers long. Carries 38,000 troops. Can conquer entire star systems by sheer intimidation and terror. Lord Vader's personal command ship.
name: Executor

dark_side_text: If you occupy with Tarkin, Piett or any admiral, your starships may 'react' to \ul Executor's\ul0  location.
gametext: If you control, your starships may move away from battle at \ul Executor's\ul0  location as a 'react'.   If you occupy with Tarkin, Piett or any admiral, your starships may 'react' to \ul Executor's\ul0  location.
light_side_text: If you control, your starships may move away from battle at \ul Executor's\ul0  location as a 'react'.
name: Executor: Comm Station

dark_side_text: If an Imperial leader here, \ul Executor\ul0  is power +1 for each \ul Executor\ul0  site on table.
gametext: If you control, only you may move \ul Executor\ul0  during opponent's move phase.   If an Imperial leader here, \ul Executor\ul0  is power +1 for each \ul Executor\ul0  site on table.
light_side_text: If you control, only you may move \ul Executor\ul0  during opponent's move phase.
name: Executor: Control Station

dark_side_text: If Vader or Emperor on table, your Force generation is +1 here (+2 if both).
gametext: Force drain +1 here. If Vader or Emperor on table, your Force generation is +1 here (+2 if both).
light_side_text: Force drain +1 here.
name: Executor: Holotheatre

dark_side_text: During your move phase, you may move free between here and \ul Executor\ul0  or any \ul Executor\ul0  site.
gametext: If you control, opponent's Main Corridor game text is canceled.   During your move phase, you may move free between here and \ul Executor\ul0  or any \ul Executor\ul0  site.
light_side_text: If you control, opponent's Main Corridor game text is canceled.
name: Executor: Main Corridor

dark_side_text: If Vader alone here, once per turn, may apply his ability to draw battle destiny at any system.
gametext: If you occupy, opponent's Meditation Chamber game text is canceled.   If Vader alone here, once per turn, may apply his ability to draw battle destiny at any system.
light_side_text: If you occupy, opponent's Meditation Chamber game text is canceled.
name: Executor: Meditation Chamber

gametext: Deploy on Dagobah: Cave. Target an apprentice on Dagobah. All Jedi Test game text is suspended. If target present during any battle phase, opponent draws destiny. If destiny < 4, you retrieve 2 Force (also, if destiny = 0, target is lost). Otherwise, Utinni Effect canceled.
lore: "That place is strong with the dark side of the Force. A domain of evil it is. In you must go."
name: Failure At The Cave

gametext: Opponent must choose to lose either 2 Force from hand or 1 Force from top of Reserve Deck.
lore: "I'm not afraid." "Oh. You will be." One of the lessons Luke learned was that fear of the unknown can be stronger than fear of the known.
name: Fear

gametext: Deploy on an Imperial of ability < 5 present with Vader, Emperor or one of your admirals, generals, or moffs. Imperial gains \b leader\b0  skill, is power +1, and is immune to Demotion, Report to Lord Vader, and What is Thy Bidding, My Master?. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: Imperial officers are fiercely competitive, especially on the \ul Executor\ul0. Lord Vader's flagship is a place where devious political calculation prospers. The naive are doomed to failure.
name: Field Promotion

gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on your Star Destroyer. Your other starships may move as a 'react' to same system or sector (for free). If starship lost, you lose X Force, where X = starship's armor. (Immune to your Alter.)
lore: After the Battle of Yavin, it was politically necessary to demonstrate the unstoppable might of the Empire. The \ul Executor\ul0  and Death Squadron ensured this objective.
name: Flagship

gametext: During your control phase, peek at opponent's hand and target one non-Interrupt card you find there that has a deploy cost < total number of [Light Side Force Icon] icons on table. Opponent must deploy a card of that title by the end of your next turn, or lose a card of that title from hand (if possible).
lore: "Rrraaaarrr!"
name: Frustration

gametext: Deploy on opponent's character. Subtracts 2 from that character's training destiny draws. OR Deploy on an opponent's pilot at a site. During each of opponent's move phases, opponent must choose to move that character, lose that character or lose 1 Force.
lore: "All his life has he looked away. To the future, to the horizon. Never his mind on where he was! Hmm? What he was doing! Hm."
name: He Is Not Ready

gametext: USED: Cancel Transmission Terminated. LOST: Take one Imperial or Visage Of The Emperor into hand from Used Pile; reshuffle.
lore: The Empire uses a real-time \b hologram\b0  communication network. Provides extensive coordination in battles, blockades and searches. Allows rapid deployment and reinforcement.
name: HoloNet Transmission

gametext: Deploys and moves like a starfighter. May add 1 pilot (must be smuggler or bounty hunter), 6 passengers and 1 vehicle. Immune to attrition < 4 while Bossk piloting. Has ship-docking capability.
lore: Controlled by state-of-the-art voice-activated X10-D computers. Internal sensors and security systems monitor prisoner activity. Modified for Bossk's Trandoshan physiology.
name: Hound's Tooth

gametext: Deploy on one opponent's unique (*) starship at a location you do not occupy. When starship is targeted by any tractor beam or ion cannon, subtract 2 from maneuver. If starship is captured or lost, lose Effect and opponent must lose 3 Force (5 if \ul Falcon\ul0).
lore: Like nerf herders herding nerfs, Imperial commanders often use TIE fighters to drive fleeing Rebel ships into tractor beam range.
name: I Want That Ship

gametext: May add 1 pilot (must be a smuggler or bounty hunter) and 2 passengers. Maneuver +3 and immune to attrition < 3 if IG-88 piloting. Ion Cannon may deploy aboard.
lore: IG-88's assault starfighter. Custom designed. Boasts a Kuat Galaxy-15 engine from a Nebulon-B frigate. Heavy ion cannon often used to disable starships before boarding.
name: IG-2000

characteristics: \b Black Sun agent\b0, \b bounty hunter\b0, assassin
gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. May 'assassinate' any character at same site hit by IG-88 (victim is immediately lost). May use two different weapons. May initiate battle and be battled. Immune to Restraining Bolt and purchase.
lore: \b Bounty hunter\b0. Went berserk upon activation. Murdered all designers at Holowan Mechanicals. IG-88's outstanding "dismantle on sight" warrant ignored by Darth Vader.
name: IG-88

gametext: Deploy on IG-88, or use 2 Force to deploy on any other bounty hunter. May target a non-droid character using 3 Force. Draw destiny. Target is power, forfeit and landspeed = 0 until end of your next turn if destiny +1 > ability.
lore: Menotor DAS-430 electromagnetic projectile launcher. Often mistaken for a blaster rifle. Fires small hollow darts filled with neurotoxin which cause temporary paralysis.
name: IG-88's Neural Inhibitor

gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on IG-88, 4 on your other warrior. Adds 2 to power. May target X non-droid characters or creatures using X Force. Draw destiny for each. If destiny = 0, character is power -1 and forfeit -1 until end of turn. If destiny -1 > defense value, target hit.
lore: IG-88's personal favorite for mass destruction. Rapid-fire fusion plasma bursts are extremely effective against multiple targets. Not widely used due to incidental damage.
name: IG-88's Pulse Cannon

gametext: If opponent just retrieved Force, opponent must lose X Force, where X = one-half the number of cards retrieved (round up).
lore: "ConcentraaAAATE!"
name: Imbalance

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting a Star Destroyer, also draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.
lore: Warrant Officer Bachenkall is typical of the many graduates of the Imperial Training Academy on Raithal. The sector naval school trains pilots in capital starship helm tactics.
name: Imperial Helmsman

gametext: Insert in opponent's Reserve Deck. When Effect reaches top it is lost and opponent may not initiate any battles for remainder of turn. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: "A Jedi uses the Force for knowledge and defense, never for attack."
name: Knowledge And Defense

gametext: During your control phase, use 1 Force to move one of your [Dagobah] characters of ability > 1 to any [Cloud City] location where you have presence. If moving to a Cloud City site, this movement is free and you do not need presence.
lore: "Lando's not a system, he's a man." Regardless of where Rebels flee, dark agents are sure to follow.
name: Lando System?

gametext: When at a site, may draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. Immune to attrition < X, where X = number of opponent's aliens present.
lore: Commander of \ul Executor\ul0  bridge pit crews. Native of Brentaal. Participated in the subjugation of Ithor, Kashyyyk, Firro, Sinton and other planets populated by non-humans.
name: Lieutenant Commander Ardan

gametext: While at a Death Star or \ul Executor\ul0  site, your troopers deploy free there and are power and forfeit +1 there, and may use 1 Force to take one Tactical Support into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
lore: Chief of security and political officer on \ul Executor\ul0. Responsible for ensuring the loyalty of his fellow officers. Disapproved of Vader's unwillingness to simply kill Skywalker.
name: Lieutenant Suba

gametext: Power +2 when at an \ul Executor\ul0  site or same site as Tarkin or Chief Bast, or if the Death Star has been "blown away." Fear Will Keep Them In Line is destiny +2 and, when it adds 1 to your power, also adds 1 to attrition against opponent.
lore: Worked hard for a transfer to the \ul Executor\ul0. One of the many non-commissioned personnel promoted to replace the vast number of officers lost during the Death Star disaster.
name: Lieutenant Venka

gametext: Deploy on table. At the end of each player's deploy phase, if they did not deploy a location, they lose 1 Force. Effect canceled if any player deploys three or more locations in a single turn.
lore: "Mudhole? Slimy? My home this is!"
name: Location, Location, Location

gametext: If a pilot was just lost from a system or sector, deploy on that location and stack pilot here. Pilot may be rescued or captured by any capital starship present here during any move phase, and may be targeted by wespons (except during battle) as if present (treat as a starfighter with defense value = 0). Lost if no pilot here.
lore: Congratulations on purchasing the TIE/ln starfighter by Sienar. Equipped with a jettison device and distress beacon, it should provide you with years of worry-free subjugation.
name: Lost In Space

gametext: May add 2 pilots (one must be a smuggler or bounty hunter) and 3 passengers. Immune to attrition < 3 if Zuckuss piloting. Has ship-docking capability.
lore: Commissioned by a group of gand venture capitalists headed by Zuckuss. Manufactured by Byblos Drive Yards. Uses repulsor lift technology developed for combat cloud cars.
name: Mist Hunter

gametext: Deploy on a Rebel. At the end of each of opponent's battle phases, if you have presence at the location where that Rebel has presences and a battle did not take place there, opponent loses 4 Force.
lore: "Adventure, heh. Excitement, heh. A Jedi craves not these things. You are reckless."
name: Much Anger In Him

gametext: Habitat: unlimited. Parasite: Starfighter. Host's power and hyperspeed are \b cumulatively\b0  -2; while both < 1, Mynocks randomly detach one at a time (cannot attach for remainder of turn). Moves like a starfighter.
lore: Silicon-based spaceborne lifeform. Frequently called a "power sucker." Feeds on energy such as stellar radiation and electrical discharges. Absorbs minerals from starship hulks.
name: Mynock

gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on table. Any card which is 'hit' may not be used to satisfy attrition. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: "Sir, we just lost the main rear deflector shield. One more direct hit on the back quarter and we're done for!"
name: Precision Targeting

gametext: Deploy on a bomber. When you Force drain at same system, may target a related interior site. Draw destiny. Site 'collapsed' if destiny > 4. May fire in Bombing Run battle. Draw destiny. All characters, starships and vehicles with that destiny number at same site are lost.
lore: Proton-scattering energy warheads. Especially effective against ray- and energy-shielded targets. Ineffective against particle deflector.
name: Proton Bombs

gametext: May add 1 pilot (must be a smuggler or bounty hunter) and 1 passenger. Immune to attrition < 3 if Dengar piloting. Deploy -3 when deploying with Dengar. Boosted TIE Cannon may deploy aboard.
lore: Old Corellian Engineering Corporation starfighter. Has outdated Class Three hyperdrive, but high sublight speed capability. Easy to maintain. Owned by Dengar.
name: Punishing One

dark_side_text: All your troopers are destiny +1 (+2 if you control). Tactical Support is a Used Interrupt.
gametext: If you occupy, opponent's Raithal game text is canceled.   All your troopers are destiny +1 (+2 if you control). Tactical Support is a Used Interrupt.
light_side_text: If you occupy, opponent's Raithal game text is canceled.
name: Raithal

gametext: If any bounty hunter is defending a battle alone, add one battle destiny. OR If Bossk, Greedo or Boba Fett is defending a battle alone, add two battle destiny.
lore: Rek guza kias n'ek kriesuk zief. Rek res fesruk T'doshok kulesuk luk g'razzurg koref selukra fes k'nel. Kren'ef, T'doshok res luk rek grien forek res fel luraken.
name: Res Luk Ra'auf

gametext: Deploy on an asteroid sector and specify starting direction. Every move phase, moves to next adjacent asteroid sector (reversing direction as necessary). Where present, adds 2 to asteroid destiny. May be targeted by starship weapons (defense value= 3).
lore: "We're gonna get pulverized if we stay out here much longer."
name: Rogue Asteroid

gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Once per turn, you may lose 1 Force to draw the top card of your Reserve Deck into your hand. If that card is a space creature, you may immediately deploy it for free.
lore: To test his theory that he was not in a cave, Han blasted the floor. He was right.
name: Shot In The Dark

gametext: Cancel Death Star Plans, The Professor, Bacta Tank, How Did We Get Into This Mess?, Shoo! Shoo! or Thank The Maker.
lore: Some droids are disliked due to their annoying personality. Several highly publicized berserk assassin droid incidents haven't helped their public image.
name: Shut Him Up Or Shut Him Down

gametext: * Ferocity = destiny - 3. Habitat: planet sites (except Hoth and Tatooine) and Dark Waters. \b Cumulatively\b0  absorbs (temporarily cancels) one (Light Side Force icon) icon present. Parasite: None.
lore: Slow, omnivorous swamp forager. Eats insects. Seeks damp, dark environments strong with the Force.
name: Sleen

gametext: During a battle, lose 1 Force. \b Cumulatively\b0  adds 1 to attrition against opponent.
lore: "That was no laser blast..."
name: Something Hit Us!

gametext: * Ferocity = two destiny. Habitat: Big One (Cave is now Belly). Attacks starfighters (defeated cards are eaten or relocated to Belly, opponent of victim chooses). Once per turn, may open or close mouth.
lore: Gigantic silicon-based lifeform. Exists in the vacuum of space. Devours small vessels whole. Has difficulty keeping its modified light freighters down.
name: Space Slug

dark_side_text: Your TIEs deploy -2 here. You may shuttle, transfer, embark and disembark here for free.
gametext: Starships captured by Star Destroyer go here and may be Besieged. Immune to Revolution.   Your TIEs deploy -2 here. You may shuttle, transfer, embark and disembark here for free.
light_side_text: Starships captured by Star Destroyer go here and may be Besieged. Immune to Revolution.
name: Star Destroyer: Launch Bay

gametext: Deploy on any Effect or Utinni Effect (except those immune to Alter). Once during each of owner's draw phases, if you occupy an asteroid sector, owner must choose to either lose 1 Force or lose that Effect or Utinni Effect. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: An asteroid looming in one's path can force a quick decision. One must choose, but choose wisely. This pilot chose poorly.
name: Sudden Impact

gametext: Deploy -1 to same system as any Imperial capital starship. May add 1 pilot. Boosted TIE Cannon may deploy aboard.
lore: Design based on Lord Vader's prototype Advanced x1. Manufactured until replaced by the more economical TIE Interceptor. Equipped with deflector shields and a hyperdrive.
name: TIE Avenger

gametext: Power +2 during a Bombing Run battle. Permanent pilot provides ability of 1. At any time during your turn, may use 1 Force to 'diffuse' (lose or return to hand) any one Orbital Mine present.
lore: Because fleet orbital bombardment often destroyed entire cities, the double-pod TIE surface assault starfighter was developed to allow more precise and controlled targeting.
name: TIE Bomber

gametext: Cancel Egregious Pilot Error, Out Of Nowhere, Collision! or Don't Get Cocky. OR Use 1 Force to subtract 3 from all asteroid destiny draws against you for remainder of turn.
lore: Aoooga! Aoooga!
name: Take Evasive Action

gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Once per turn, you may peek at the top three cards of your Reserve Deck. Place any two of those three in your Lost Pile.
lore: "If once you start down the dark path, forever will it dominate your destiny. Consume you it will, as it did Obi-Wan's apprentice."
name: The Dark Path

gametext: Deploy on table. Sense and Alter are Lost Interrupts. Also, when any player makes a destiny draw for Sense or Alter, and that destiny draw is successful, that player loses 2 Force. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: "Always with you what cannot be done."
name: There Is No Try

gametext: USED: Cancel Nabrun Leids. LOST: During your move phase, cancel Landing Claw. OR Cancel Hyper Escape, Closer?! or one 'react.'
lore: "I don't know how we're gonna get out of this one."
name: Those Rebels Won't Escape Us

gametext: Use 3 Force. Each player places hand onto Reserve Deck (if possible), then places Used Pile onto Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Each player then draws cards from Reserve Deck equal to the number of cards just placed from hand onto Reserve Deck (if any).
lore: Even a Jedi cannot always foresee future events.
name: Uncertain Is The Future

gametext: Use 2 Force to take one Interrupt into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
lore: "Sir! Sir! I've isolated the reverse power flux coupling!"
name: Unexpected Interruption

gametext: Habitat: planet sites (except Hoth). Parasite: Non-droid character. Each move phase, draw destiny; each time destiny > ability, add 1 to X (X starts at 0). Host is power -X (eaten if power = 0).
lore: Found on various planets throughout the galaxy. Hides among hanging vines, dropping on unsuspecting travelers that pass beneath. Kills its victims through gradual constriction.
name: Vine Snake

gametext: Lose 2 Force to deploy on \ul Executor\ul0: Holotheatre or Death Star: Conference Room. At the end of each player's turn, each player must lose 1 Force. Effect canceled if opponent controls this site. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: Palpatine's \b hologram\b0. Imposing. Ominous. Intimidating. Instrument for the evil Emperor's sinister reach across the galaxy. Used on a secret frequency of the Imperial HoloNet.
name: Visage Of The Emperor

gametext: Name an Interrupt card. Opponent must reveal entire Used Pile, without shuffling. Then you choose: USED: Opponent must lose 1 Force for each copy of that Interrupt found there. LOST: Each copy of that interrupt found there is lost.
lore: As there are very few local authorities on Dagobah, peeping astromechs can get away with just about anything.
name: Voyeur

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. May use 1 Force to take one tractor beam, Our First Catch Of The Day or Besieged into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
lore: Hard-working \ul Avenger\ul0  signal officer. Coordinates and tests tractor beam operations. Apprises \ul Executor\ul0  of his ship's activities and relays orders from the flagship to his captain.
name: Warrant Officer M'Kae

characteristics: \b Black Sun agent\b0, \b bounty hunter\b0, \b scout\b0
gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. May move for free as 'react.' Once during each battle, may use 1 Force to cause one alien of ability < 3 at same site to be forfeit = 0 for remainder of turn. Immune to attrition < 3.
lore: Male Gand. Practitioner of ancient religious findsman vocation. \b Bounty hunter\b0  and \b scout\b0. Gains surprisingly accurate information through mystical visions during meditation.
name: Zuckuss

gametext: Deploy on Zuckuss, or use 1 Force to deploy on any other bounty hunter. May target a character or creature using 2 Force. Draw destiny. Character captured if destiny -1 > defense value. Creature lost if destiny +1 > defense value.
lore: Merr-Sonn Munitions, Inc. GRS-1 Snare Rifle. Shoots liquefied shockstun mist up to 150 meters. Liquid spraynet hardens into a translucent web, confining the stunned target.
name: Zuckuss' Snare Rifle
